746:**Step 3: Run the calibration and fairness tests, and gate model promotion through governance.** A trained model is not a production model. Calibration tests check that predicted treatment effects match observed effects in held-out cohorts and in subgroups. Fairness tests check that calibration is consistent across protected subpopulations. The governance gate is a human review of the test results before the new model artifacts are promoted to production. Skip this and you ship a model with unknown calibration on the populations it will most affect.
